s to realize he is a wanted hacker. Meanwhile, Sloane\u2019s biological daughter Faith, requests her father\u2019s medical history, unintentionally forcing Sloane to confront that man: he had raped her after a college party. Sloane makes sure he\u2019ll give Faith what she asks for, lie about the circumstances of her birth, and to never contact her again, but Faith puts two and two together and thanks Sloane for giving her up for adoption in order to protect her from her biological father.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 397\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 19\n |Title           = Blarney\n |DirectedBy      = Rocky Carroll\n |WrittenBy       = Scott Williams\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|31}}\n |Viewers         = 13.65<ref name=\"17.19\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-31-2020.html|title=ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.31.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Jimmy and Kasie are held hostage in the diner Gibbs frequently visits after three armed burglars mismanage a heist at a nearby jewelry store. The leader kills their driver beforehand due to the latter spilling details to his wife, who later relays it to Vance and Sloane. A cook at the diner shoots one of the burglars in an attempt to free the patrons, later resulting in the crook\u2019s death and his fellow robbers forcing Jimmy to cut out the diamonds he had swallowed. This gives Jimmy and Kasie the idea to convince them they are bleeding internally from broken glass, saving the other patrons and ending the hostage situation.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 398\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n |Title           = The Arizona\n |DirectedBy      = James Whitmore Jr.\n |WrittenBy       = Gina Lucita Monreal\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|14}}\n |Viewers         = 13.49<ref name=\"17.20\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-14-2020.html|title=ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.14.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The team tries to verify the identity of Joe Smith, who claims to have served on the U.S.S. Arizona during the Pearl Harbor attacks and wants his ashes interred there when he dies. Meanwhile, McGee unwittingly gets roped into a family reunion of people he doesn't know.\n\nNote: This episode was dedicated to the Pearl Harbor victims as well as the first responders and those on the frontlines battling the Coronavirus pandemic.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production==\n''NCIS'' was renewed for a seventeenth season on April 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/ncis-renewed-season-17-cbs-mark-harmon-new-deal-cbs-tv-studios-1202593874/|title=''NCIS'' Renewed For Season 17 By CBS As Star & EP Mark Harmon Inks New Deal|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 11, 2019|accessdate=April 11, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411193012/https://deadline.com/2019/04/ncis-renewed-season-17-cbs-mark-harmon-new-deal-cbs-tv-studios-1202593874/|archivedate=April 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe seventeenth season of ''NCIS'' premiered on September 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/13/cbs-announces-fall-2019-2020-primetime-premiere-dates-448415/20190613cbs01/|title=CBS Announces Fall 2019\u20132020 Primetime Premiere Dates|work=[[The Futon Critic]]|date=June 13, 2019|accessdate=June 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width    = 99\n| fontsize = 90\n\n| 