liams]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|8}}\n |Viewers         = 11.19<ref name=\"17.03\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-8-2019/|title=''The Conners'' adjusts up: Tuesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 9, 2019|accessdate=October 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011040224/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-8-2019/|archive-date=October 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = After a body is found underneath a truck entering the Navy Yard, the investigation into the man's death leads them to a trailer park with a number of interesting residents; Sloane tries to get the team to talk regarding Ziva's recent appearance and departure.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 382\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Someone Else's Shoes\n |DirectedBy      = [[Michael Zinberg]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Christopher J. Waild]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|15}}\n |Viewers         = 10.87<ref name=\"17.04\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-15-2019/|title=''Mixed-ish'' adjusts down: Tuesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 16, 2019|accessdate=October 16, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191023062424/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-15-2019/|archive-date=October 23, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The NCIS team investigates a bizarre crime scene at Arlington National Cemetery which is linked to a string of attacks on homeless veterans. Also, as a punishment for lying to Director Vance regarding Ziva's sudden reappearance, McGee, Bishop and Torres will have to spend their entire day conducting evidence garage cleanup. \n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke